text: Melanie started with 5 vacuum cleaners. She sold 1/3 of them at the green house, which is 5 x 1/3 = 5/3. So she had 5 - 5/3 = 10/3 vacuum cleaners left. She sold 2 more at the red house, so she had 10/3 - 2 = 4/3 vacuum cleaners left. She sold half of what was left at the orange house, which is 4/3 / 2 = 2/3 vacuum cleaners. So she had 2/3 + 2/3 = 4/3 vacuum cleaners left. Since 4/3 is equal to 1 2/3, Melanie had 1 2/3 vacuum cleaners left. To convert this to a mixed number, we can write 1 2/3 as 1 and 1/3. So Melanie had 1 and 1/3 vacuum cleaners left. The final answer is 1 1/3

Lauren can draw 5 large-sized picture scenes per day, 36 medium-sized per day, or 49 small-sized per day. To find out how many days it will take to create all of the picture scenes, we need to divide the total number of picture scenes by the number of scenes she can draw per day.

45 large-sized scenes / 5 scenes per day = 9 days
36 medium-sized scenes / 6 scenes per day = 6 days
49 small-sized scenes / 7 scenes per day = 7 days

Since Lauren can draw 5 large-sized scenes per day, she will need 9 days to create all of the large-sized picture scenes. She can draw 36 medium-sized scenes per day, so she will need 6 days to create all of the medium-sized picture scenes. She can draw 49 small-sized scenes per day, so she will need 7 days to create all of the small-sized picture scenes.

The final answer is 9, 6, and 7.

Mike was a pen pal with 5 people. He stopped being pen pals with 2 of them. So he is still a pen pal with 5 - 2 = 3 people. Each of the 3 people sends 2 letters a week, which is 3 x 2 = 6 letters. Each letter is 5 pages long, so 6 letters * 5 pages = 30 pages. Mike responds in kind, so he also writes 30 pages. He can write a page every 6 minutes, so 30 pages / 6 pages per minute = 5 minutes. There are 60 minutes in an hour, so 5 minutes / 60 minutes per hour = 1/12 of an hour. The final answer is 1/12

There are 6 periods in a day. John has to take 2 extra classes, so he has 6 + 2 = 8 periods. Each class is 40 minutes long, so 8 periods * 40 minutes = 320 minutes. He goes to class for 5 days a week, so 320 minutes * 5 days = 1600 minutes. He spends 1/16 of his weekly minutes as extra learning time, so 1600 minutes * 1/16 = 100 minutes. 100 minutes is 100/60 = 5/3 hours. The final answer is 5/3

The average age of the group is (4 + 4 + 3 + 2) / 4 = 13 / 4 = 3.25. Since Helene is twice as old as the average age, she is 2 x 3.25 = 6.5 years old. The total age of the children is 20. So the sum of the ages of the children is 20. 20 - 6.5 = 13.5. Since the average age is 3.25, the sum of the ages of the children is 3.25 x 4 = 13. So 13.5 - 13 = 0.5. The final answer is 0.5

The cake will take 20 + 30 + 2 + 10 = 72 minutes to make. 1 hour is 60 minutes. So the cake will be ready 72 / 60 = 1.2 hours after Jordan starts making it. Since she wants to serve it at 5:00 pm, she can start making the cake at 5:00 pm - 1.2 hours = 3:48 pm. The final answer is 3:48 pm

Rose bought 12 onions and 4 potatoes. Since Rose bought 4 times the number of onions and potatoes Sophia bought, Sophia bought 12 / 4 = 3 onions and 4 / 4 = 1 potato. So Sophia bought 3 + 1 = 4 onions and 1 potato. The final answer is 4 and 1.
